          "date": "2019-04-19 16:31:09.000000000",
          "tz": 180
        },
        "subject": "LU-11023 quota: tune quota pools through LCFG",
        "message": "LU-11023 quota: tune quota pools through LCFG\n\nAdd ability to tune quota pools together\nwith LOD pools through LCFG commands.\nSince this patch each LOD pool has a \"mirror\"\nin quota pools. Quota pools are created and\nmodified together with LOD pools. Creating\nof LOD pool causes QMT to create a directory\nquota_master/dt-\"poolname\" with index files.\nFurther when/if MDT pools will be ready, QMT\nshould also create md-\"poolname\" with indexes.\nDestroying quota pool causes removing it's\ndirectory(dt-\"poolname\") with inside index\nfiles.\n\nPatch also adds a key \"-o <pool>\" to lfs setquota.\nThe key means all settings from the command\nstring should be applied to requested pool\nfor the user/grp/prj ID.\n\nCray-bug-id: LUS-5801\nChange-Id: I66131811f42ceb038b9b79d20d626576d6768926\nSigned-off-by: Sergey Cheremencev <c17829@cray.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
